<!-- OVERVIEW -->
<section class="s-light" id="overview">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="stag">Plan Overview</div>
    <h2>The 30-second version</h2>
    <p class="intro">A focused local Search campaign that drives high-intent furniture shoppers to the right product and category pages on timberandterraceva.com — and into the Short Pump showroom. The Google Business Profile is linked as a Location Asset so ads also surface in Google Maps and the local pack.</p>

    <div class="tw">
      <div class="th"><h3>Plan at a Glance</h3><p>Core settings for launch</p></div>
      <table><tbody>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Monthly budget</td><td><span class="tdt">$1,000</span> (~$33/day)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Campaign type</td><td>Search with Google Business Profile Location Asset</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Primary goal</td><td>Qualified website traffic to product / category pages + store visits</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Traffic destination</td><td>Website (category &amp; product pages) — Location Asset for Maps / store visits</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Location</td><td>Richmond / Short Pump, VA + 15-mile radius (Henrico, Goochland, Chesterfield, Powhatan)</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="tdl">Bidding</td><td>Manual CPC → Maximize Clicks / Target CPA after 30 days</td></tr>
      </tbody></table>
    </div>

    <div class="co d">
      <div class="ci">📍</div>
      <div><h3>Why Search + Location Asset?</h3><p>Furniture is a considered, local purchase — people search, compare, and want to sit in the chair before buying. Linking the Google Business Profile as a Location Asset lets the campaign show in Google Maps and the local pack, capturing both "buy now online" and "visit the showroom" intent from one budget.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- GMB -->
<section class="s-mid" id="gmb">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="stag">Foundation</div>
    <h2>Google Business Profile &amp; Site Readiness</h2>
    <p class="intro">The Location Asset pulls directly from the Business Profile, and ads send shoppers to live product pages. Both must be accurate and linked to the Google Ads account before launch.</p>
    <div class="c2">
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag t">Business Profile</span>
        <h3>Profile checklist</h3>
        <ul class="ck">
          <li>Profile verified &amp; claimed at google.com/business</li>
          <li>Name, address (3401 Cox Rd, Richmond VA 23233) &amp; phone match the website exactly</li>
          <li>Category set to "Furniture store" + relevant secondary categories (Outdoor furniture store, Amish furniture)</li>
          <li>Hours correct: Mon &amp; Thu–Sat 10–5, Sun 1–5, Tue/Wed closed</li>
          <li>20+ high-quality photos (showroom, outdoor displays, indoor sets, room styling)</li>
          <li>Products/services listed: Adirondacks, gliders, fire tables, dining, bedroom, living room</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag a">Website</span>
        <h3>Landing page checklist</h3>
        <ul class="ck todo">
          <li>Each ad group points to its matching category page (not the homepage)</li>
          <li>"What's In Stock" pages load fast on mobile and show current pricing</li>
          <li>Store address, hours &amp; "Get Directions" visible above the fold</li>
          <li>Phone number is click-to-call on mobile</li>
          <li>Clear CTA on every page: "Visit the Showroom" / "Shop In-Stock"</li>
          <li>Admin / linked access granted to the Twist team</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- STRUCTURE -->
<section class="s-light" id="structure">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="stag">Campaign Structure</div>
    <h2>One campaign, four ad groups</h2>
    <p class="intro">A single local Search campaign keeps budget and negatives centralized. Four tightly themed ad groups let each product line use its own keywords, copy, and landing page.</p>

    <div class="co">
      <div class="ci">🗂️</div>
      <div>
        <h3>Campaign: Timber &amp; Terrace — Richmond Local Search</h3>
        <p><strong>Budget:</strong> $1,000/mo (~$33/day) · <strong>Bidding:</strong> Manual CPC · <strong>Networks:</strong> Search only (no Search Partners, no Display) · <strong>Location:</strong> Richmond + 15-mi radius, "Presence" only · <strong>Language:</strong> English · <strong>Schedule:</strong> All week, 7 AM–9 PM (research happens outside store hours)</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="rr" style="margin-top:28px">
      <div class="rc"><div class="rb">~40%</div><p>Outdoor — Adirondacks &amp; Poly<span>Seasonal core driver</span></p></div>
      <div class="rc"><div class="rb a">~30%</div><p>Outdoor — Patio, Dining &amp; Fire<span>Higher ticket sets</span></p></div>
      <div class="rc"><div class="rb g">~25%</div><p>Indoor — Amish Solid Wood<span>New expansion line</span></p></div>
    </div>
    <p class="intro" style="margin-bottom:0">Remaining ~5% holds <strong>Ad Group 4 — Brand</strong> to defend "Timber &amp; Terrace" and "Poly Furniture of Williamsburg" searches at low cost. Suggested split is a starting point — shift toward whatever converts after the first month.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- KEYWORDS -->
<section class="s-mid" id="keywords">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="stag">Keywords</div>
    <h2>Keywords by ad group</h2>
    <p class="intro">Phrase match for reach with control; exact match on the strongest converters. Negatives route traffic to the right ad group and block low-intent queries.</p>

    <!-- AG1 -->
    <div class="wc" style="margin-bottom:20px">
      <span class="tag t">Ad Group 1</span>
      <h3>Outdoor — Adirondacks &amp; Poly Chairs</h3>
      <p>Their signature, in-stock, ready-to-buy category. Strong "near me" intent. Suggested CPC: $1.50–$3.50.</p>
      <div class="lbl">Phrase match</div>
      <div class="kw"><span>"adirondack chairs richmond va"</span><span>"poly adirondack chairs near me"</span><span>"poly furniture richmond va"</span><span>"porch rockers near me"</span><span>"outdoor rocking chairs richmond"</span><span>"poly outdoor furniture short pump"</span><span>"weatherproof patio chairs va"</span><span>"polywood chairs near me"</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Exact match</div>
      <div class="kw ex"><span>[adirondack chairs richmond va]</span><span>[poly furniture richmond va]</span><span>[porch rockers richmond]</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Negative keywords</div>
      <div class="kw neg"><span>cheap</span><span>used</span><span>plans</span><span>diy</span><span>how to build</span><span>plastic walmart</span><span>cushions only</span><span>repair</span><span>indoor</span><span>dining</span><span>bedroom</span></div>
    </div>

    <!-- AG2 -->
    <div class="wc" style="margin-bottom:20px">
      <span class="tag a">Ad Group 2</span>
      <h3>Outdoor — Patio, Dining, Gliders &amp; Fire Tables</h3>
      <p>Higher-ticket outdoor sets and seating. Suggested CPC: $2–$4.50.</p>
      <div class="lbl">Phrase match</div>
      <div class="kw"><span>"patio furniture richmond va"</span><span>"outdoor dining sets near me"</span><span>"poly patio dining table va"</span><span>"outdoor deep seating richmond"</span><span>"swivel glider chair near me"</span><span>"fire table richmond va"</span><span>"outdoor furniture short pump"</span><span>"patio furniture store near me"</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Exact match</div>
      <div class="kw ex"><span>[patio furniture richmond va]</span><span>[outdoor dining sets richmond]</span><span>[fire table richmond va]</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Negative keywords</div>
      <div class="kw neg"><span>cheap</span><span>used</span><span>rental</span><span>cushions only</span><span>covers</span><span>repair</span><span>clearance walmart</span><span>indoor</span><span>bedroom</span><span>adirondack</span></div>
    </div>

    <!-- AG3 -->
    <div class="wc" style="margin-bottom:20px">
      <span class="tag g">Ad Group 3</span>
      <h3>Indoor — Amish Solid Wood Furniture</h3>
      <p>Dining, bedroom &amp; living room — the expansion line. Higher intent &amp; margin. Suggested CPC: $2.50–$5.</p>
      <div class="lbl">Phrase match</div>
      <div class="kw"><span>"amish furniture richmond va"</span><span>"solid wood dining table near me"</span><span>"amish dining set richmond"</span><span>"solid wood bedroom furniture va"</span><span>"amish furniture store near me"</span><span>"handmade wood furniture richmond"</span><span>"solid wood furniture short pump"</span><span>"real wood dining table richmond va"</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Exact match</div>
      <div class="kw ex"><span>[amish furniture richmond va]</span><span>[solid wood furniture richmond va]</span><span>[amish dining set richmond]</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Negative keywords</div>
      <div class="kw neg"><span>cheap</span><span>used</span><span>ikea</span><span>particle board</span><span>diy</span><span>plans</span><span>repair</span><span>refinishing</span><span>outdoor</span><span>adirondack</span><span>patio</span></div>
    </div>

    <!-- AG4 -->
    <div class="wc">
      <span class="tag t">Ad Group 4</span>
      <h3>Brand</h3>
      <p>Cheap defense of branded searches across both showrooms. Suggested CPC: $0.50–$1.50.</p>
      <div class="lbl">Phrase &amp; exact match</div>
      <div class="kw ex"><span>[timber and terrace]</span><span>[timber & terrace richmond]</span><span>"timber and terrace furniture"</span><span>"poly furniture of williamsburg"</span><span>"timber terrace short pump"</span></div>
      <div class="lbl">Negative keywords</div>
      <div class="kw neg"><span>jobs</span><span>careers</span><span>reviews complaints</span><span>hours wrong</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- AD COPY -->
<section class="s-light" id="copy">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="stag">Ad Copy</div>
    <h2>Responsive Search Ads</h2>
    <p class="intro">One RSA per ad group, 15 headlines and 4 descriptions each. Headlines 1–2 are pinned to anchor location and offer; Google rotates the rest. Below are AG1 (Outdoor) and AG3 (Indoor); AG2 and AG4 follow the same pinning pattern with patio- and brand-specific copy.</p>

    <div class="co" style="margin-top:0;margin-bottom:24px">
      <div class="ci">📌</div>
      <div><h3>Pinning pattern (all ad groups)</h3><p><strong>Position 1 (pinned):</strong> Headline 1 — location + service. <strong>Position 2 (pinned):</strong> Headline 2 — key differentiator (Amish-made / in-stock). <strong>Position 3 (unpinned):</strong> Google rotates Headlines 3–15.</p></div>
    </div>

    <!-- RSA 1 -->
    <div class="tw" style="margin-bottom:24px">
      <div class="th"><h3>Ad Group 1 — Outdoor (Adirondacks &amp; Poly)</h3><p>1 RSA · 15 headlines · 4 descriptions</p></div>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th style="width:48px">#</th><th>Headline</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="tdt">1</td><td class="tdl">Adirondack Chairs — Richmond <em>(pin 1)</em></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="tdt">2</td><td class="tdl">Amish-Made Poly Furniture <em>(pin 2)</em></td></tr>
