    <h2>Two phases</h2>
    <div class="tw">
      <div class="th"><h3>Bidding Roadmap</h3><p>Build history first, then automate</p></div>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Phase</th><th>Timing</th><th>Strategy</th><th>Setting</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="tdl">Phase 1</td><td>Days 1–30</td><td class="tdt">Manual CPC</td><td>Max CPC by ad group: $3.50 (AG1), $4.50 (AG2), $5 (AG3), $1.50 (AG4)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="tdl">Phase 2</td><td>After 30 days + 15+ conversions</td><td class="tdt">Maximize Clicks / Target CPA</td><td>If conversions are firm, set Target CPA at 1.5× observed cost per conversion; otherwise Max Clicks with a CPC cap</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <div class="co w" style="margin:0;border-radius:0;border-left:0;border-right:0;border-bottom:0">
        <div class="ci">⚠️</div>
        <div><h3>Don't automate too early</h3><p>Manual CPC in Phase 1 keeps full control while the account builds history. With furniture's longer consideration cycle, hold Manual CPC until you have 15+ tracked conversions (store visits, calls, or key page views) — switching sooner makes automated bidding erratic.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

