    <div class="c2">
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag t">Week 1</span>
        <h3>Sanity checks</h3>
        <ul class="ck">
          <li>Conversions appearing in Google Ads</li>
          <li>Profile views up vs. baseline</li>
          <li>No disapproved ads or keywords</li>
          <li>Budget pacing near $33/day</li>
          <li>Search Terms report reviewed</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag a">Weeks 2–4</span>
        <h3>Early optimization</h3>
        <ul class="ck">
          <li>Weekly Search Terms review — add negatives &amp; new keywords</li>
          <li>Pause any RSA headline/description rated "Low"</li>
          <li>Confirm spend skews to the best-converting ad groups</li>
          <li>Verify ads land on the right category pages</li>
          <li>If an ad group hits its CPC cap, assess raising it or shifting budget</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag g">Month 1</span>
        <h3>End-of-month review</h3>
        <ul class="ck">
          <li>Total spend vs. $1,000 budget</li>
          <li>Store visits, calls &amp; directions tracked</li>
          <li>Cost per store visit / lead by ad group</li>
          <li>Profile views, calls, directions: before vs. after</li>
          <li>Reconcile ad leads with actual in-store sales</li>
          <li>Pause any ad group spending with no leads</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="wc">
        <span class="tag t">Months 2–3</span>
        <h3>Scaling decisions</h3>
        <ul class="ck">
          <li>15+ conversions → switch to Target CPA at 1.5× cost/conv</li>
          <li>Add fresh RSA variations; rotate copy</li>
          <li>Add Promotion assets for seasonal "Special Buys"</li>
          <li>Shift budget toward outdoor in spring/summer, indoor in fall/winter</li>
          <li>If results are healthy &amp; budget fully spent, scale to $1,500/mo</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

